============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/6-8a6c985/feedback.md`. Key findings:

**Case 1 (Baked Eggs):** Iteration 6's continuation protection removes the prefix single-line (`Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce`) but not the suffix single (`& Coriander`). `& Coriander` passes all hard filters and may survive the threshold. Since the full join contains `& coriander` as a substring, the dedup "shorter wins" rule eliminates the join. The fix addressed the prefix-side but missed the suffix-side.

**Case 2 (SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS):** Two issues:
1. The OCR text has `/` in line 55, but the filename encodes the expected title with `:` (because `/` is illegal in filenames). Even if the algorithm extracts the correct join, it outputs `/ COTTAGE CHEESE` while `titles_match` looks for `: COTTAGE CHEESE` — an exact mismatch. This is primarily an **evaluation mismatch**, not an algorithm bug.
2. The `-0.15` truncation penalty on `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)` may not reliably demote it below threshold across varying embedding score distributions.
