{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012yjbFAd2Cu4MaR2CptvMVo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→BUNS\n     2→ssekart\n     3→alled out into names.\n     4→The\n     5→favoured by\n     6→the julgalt.\n     7→ly named as you e right, esting n on\n     8→cover the bun\n     9→ver\n    10→Before raisins back\n    11→baking.\n    12→and leave into\n    13→the rising.\n    14→Preheat the oven to 225°C/435-VI0..\n    15→Brush the buns lightly\n    16→Bake until nicely\n    17→Bakc\n    18→golden.\n    19→or they will be the driest\n    20→The cooking time\n    21→The cod\n    22→shape you have made but should be 15 minutes.\n    23→Types of bun shapes, from\n    24→Lop\n    25→right: gullvagn. fuvagn, lessekarz tank\n    26→lilja. julgalt, and julkuse.\n    27→hila./\n    28→For image see page 279\n    29→FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\n    30→eden)\n    31→ing time: 2 hours\n    32→5)\n    33→utter\n    34→ablespoons)\n    35→1)\n    36→190\n    37→oz (to cup) segar\n    38→plan i tateleypo\n    39→extra for dusting\n    40→up rong wheat Bour, pl\n    41→135 g/415 oz (1 stick) butter, at room\n    42→Bes Wash (pages 73 4)\n    43→For the topping raisins, soaked in water pearl sugar, to taste\n    44→for at least an hour.\n    45→Add the saffron to the vodka and leave to infuse\n    46→Meanwhile, make the dough. Melt the butter in a pan age. Disson heat to body temperature (37°C/98.6°F). Dissolve the yeast in the milk and butter mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer. Add the salt, 1 tablespoon of the sugar and most of the four and work with the dough hook for 5-10 min-utes.\n    47→Cover the bowl with a clean dish towel and\n    48→leave the dough to rise for 1 hour.\n    49→Stir the butter with the remaining sugar in a bowl until fuffy, then add the egg and the saffron and vodka infusion and stir. When the dough has finished rising, add the saffron and butter mix and the rest of the four while working the dough with the dough hook in the stand mixer.\n    50→Line 2 baking sheets with baking (parchment) paper. Tip the dough out onto a lightly floured work counter and knead it for a minute. Divide the dough into 30 equal pieces and shape them into your choice of saffron buns (see illustrations opposite). Put the buns on the prepared baking cover with clean dish towels and leave to\n    51→rise for 30 minutes.\n    52→Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 220°C/425°F/Gas Mark 7. Brush the buns with the egg wash and sprinkle with raisins and/or pearl sugar. Bake for about to minutes, then leave to cool on wire racks.\n    53→For image see page 279\n    54→SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\n    55→/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\n    56→trutter med kesells / kurg (Sweden\n    57→Preparation and cooking rime 2 hour ising rime: r5s hour\n    58→Makes: 30 buns\n    59→100 g/3 oz (7 tablespoons) butter\n    60→500ml/17 fl oz (2 cups plus 2 tablespoons) milk\n    61→50g/2 oz fresh yeast (pages 58-61)\n    62→250 g/g oz. (1 cup) quark or cottage cheese\n    63→1 g/o.04 oz saffron (page 75)\n    64→150 g/5 oz (¼ cup) sugar\n    65→1 teaspoon salt\n    66→950g/2 lb 2 oz (7½ cups) strong wheat flour. plus extra for dusting\n    67→Egg Wash (pages 73-4)\n    68→To decorate\n    69→raisins, soaked in water and drained pearl sugar, to sprinkle\n    70→Melt the butter in a pan, then add the milk and heat to body temperature (37°C/98.6°F). Dissolve the yeast in the milk and butter mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer. Add the quark, saffron. sugar, salt and most of the flour and work the dough with the dough hook, starting at low speed. for 5-10 minutes. Cover the bowl with a clean dish towel and leave to rise for 45 minutes.\n    71→Line several baking sheets with baking (parch-ment) paper. Tip the dough out onto a lightly floured work counter and knead it for a minute.\n    72→Divide the dough into 30 equal pieces and shape them into your choice of saffron bun (see illustrations opposite). Put the buns on the prepared baking sheets, cover with clean dish towels and leave to rise for another 45 minutes.\n    73→Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 200°C/400°F/Gas Mark 6. Brush the buns with the egg wash and sprinkle on the raisins and pearl sugar to decorate.\n    74→Bake for about 1o minutes, or until golden. Leave to cool on wire racks.\n    75→For image see page 279\n    76→277 Recipes / Sweet pastries leavened with yeast\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"220c2158-c29d-4d36-918e-39dcfccb497b","uuid":"9d7d5844-1061-4f20-a93d-ed270f065fb6","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D).real.txt","content":"BUNS\nssekart\nalled out into names.\nThe\nfavoured by\nthe julgalt.\nly named as you e right, esting n on\ncover the bun\nver\nBefore raisins back\nbaking.\nand leave into\nthe rising.\nPreheat the oven to 225°C/435-VI0..\nBrush the buns lightly\nBake until nicely\nBakc\ngolden.\nor they will be the driest\nThe cooking time\nThe cod\nshape you have made but should be 15 minutes.\nTypes of bun shapes, from\nLop\nright: gullvagn. fuvagn, lessekarz tank\nlilja. julgalt, and julkuse.\nhila./\nFor image see page 279\nFRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\neden)\ning time: 2 hours\n5)\nutter\nablespoons)\n1)\n190\noz (to cup) segar\nplan i tateleypo\nextra for dusting\nup rong wheat Bour, pl\n135 g/415 oz (1 stick) butter, at room\nBes Wash (pages 73 4)\nFor the topping raisins, soaked in water pearl sugar, to taste\nfor at least an hour.\nAdd the saffron to the vodka and leave to infuse\nMeanwhile, make the dough. Melt the butter in a pan age. Disson heat to body temperature (37°C/98.6°F). Dissolve the yeast in the milk and butter mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer. Add the salt, 1 tablespoon of the sugar and most of the four and work with the dough hook for 5-10 min-utes.\nCover the bowl with a clean dish towel and\nleave the dough to rise for 1 hour.\nStir the butter with the remaining sugar in a bowl until fuffy, then add the egg and the saffron and vodka infusion and stir. When the dough has finished rising, add the saffron and butter mix and the rest of the four while working the dough with the dough hook in the stand mixer.\nLine 2 baking sheets with baking (parchment) paper. Tip the dough out onto a lightly floured work counter and knead it for a minute. Divide the dough into 30 equal pieces and shape them into your choice of saffron buns (see illustrations opposite). Put the buns on the prepared baking cover with clean dish towels and leave to\nrise for 30 minutes.\nMeanwhile, preheat the oven to 220°C/425°F/Gas Mark 7. Brush the buns with the egg wash and sprinkle with raisins and/or pearl sugar. Bake for about to minutes, then leave to cool on wire racks.\nFor image see page 279\nSAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\n/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\ntrutter med kesells / kurg (Sweden\nPreparation and cooking rime 2 hour ising rime: r5s hour\nMakes: 30 buns\n100 g/3 oz (7 tablespoons) butter\n500ml/17 fl oz (2 cups plus 2 tablespoons) milk\n50g/2 oz fresh yeast (pages 58-61)\n250 g/g oz. (1 cup) quark or cottage cheese\n1 g/o.04 oz saffron (page 75)\n150 g/5 oz (¼ cup) sugar\n1 teaspoon salt\n950g/2 lb 2 oz (7½ cups) strong wheat flour. plus extra for dusting\nEgg Wash (pages 73-4)\nTo decorate\nraisins, soaked in water and drained pearl sugar, to sprinkle\nMelt the butter in a pan, then add the milk and heat to body temperature (37°C/98.6°F). Dissolve the yeast in the milk and butter mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer. Add the quark, saffron. sugar, salt and most of the flour and work the dough with the dough hook, starting at low speed. for 5-10 minutes. Cover the bowl with a clean dish towel and leave to rise for 45 minutes.\nLine several baking sheets with baking (parch-ment) paper. Tip the dough out onto a lightly floured work counter and knead it for a minute.\nDivide the dough into 30 equal pieces and shape them into your choice of saffron bun (see illustrations opposite). Put the buns on the prepared baking sheets, cover with clean dish towels and leave to rise for another 45 minutes.\nMeanwhile, preheat the oven to 200°C/400°F/Gas Mark 6. Brush the buns with the egg wash and sprinkle on the raisins and pearl sugar to decorate.\nBake for about 1o minutes, or until golden. Leave to cool on wire racks.\nFor image see page 279\n277 Recipes / Sweet pastries leavened with yeast","numLines":76,"startLine":1,"totalLines":76}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MJ4i2bGfNT1i2kVDU3xS44","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Title Extraction\n     3→ * Extracts potential recipe title from OCR text using heuristics or semantic embeddings\n     4→ */\n     5→\n     6→import { cosineSimilarity } from \"./embeddings\";\n     7→\n     8→export type EmbedFn = (text: string) => Promise<Array<number>>;\n     9→\n    10→const TITLE_REFERENCE =\n    11→  \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\";\n    12→const HEADER_REFERENCE =\n    13→  \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\";\n    14→const NOISE_REFERENCE =\n    15→  \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\";\n    16→\n    17→/**\n    18→ * Measurement units commonly found in ingredient lists\n    19→ */\n    20→const MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS = [\n    21→  \"cup\",\n    22→  \"cups\",\n    23→  \"tbsp\",\n    24→  \"tsp\",\n    25→  \"tablespoon\",\n    26→  \"teaspoon\",\n    27→  \"oz\",\n    28→  \"lb\",\n    29→  \"gram\",\n    30→  \"grams\",\n    31→  \"kg\",\n    32→  \"ml\",\n    33→  \"liter\",\n    34→  \"pinch\",\n    35→  \"dash\",\n    36→  \"handful\",\n    37→];\n    38→\n    39→/**\n    40→ * Patterns that identify recipe metadata lines (not titles)\n    41→ */\n    42→const METADATA_PATTERNS = [\n    43→  /^(SERVES?|MAKES?|YIELDS?)\\b/i,\n    44→  /^(PREP(ARATION)?|COOK(ING)?|PROOF|RISING|FERMENTATION|REST(ING)?)\\s*(AND\\s*)?(COOK(ING)?)?\\s*TIME/i,\n    45→  /^SAMPLE\\s+SCHEDULE\\b/i,\n    46→  /^BULK\\s+FERMENTATION\\b/i,\n    47→  /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i,\n    48→];\n    49→\n    50→/**\n    51→ * Single-word non-title words — standalone OCR fragments unlikely to be recipe titles\n    52→ */\n    53→const NON_TITLE_WORDS = new Set([\n    54→  \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"are\", \"was\",\n    55→  \"has\", \"his\", \"her\", \"its\", \"our\", \"who\", \"how\", \"may\", \"new\", \"now\",\n    56→  \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\", \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n    57→  \"buns\", \"with\",\n    58→]);\n    59→\n    60→function looksLikeIngredient(line: string): boolean {\n    61→  const lowerLine = line.toLowerCase();\n    62→  return MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => lowerLine.includes(pattern));\n    63→}\n    64→\n    65→function startsWithNumber(line: string): boolean {\n    66→  return /^\\s*\\d/.test(line);\n    67→}\n    68→\n    69→function isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n    70→  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n    71→  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n    72→}\n    73→\n    74→function looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n    75→  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n    76→}\n    77→\n    78→function isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n    79→  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n    80→  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n    81→\n    82→  // Check vowel ratio — English/Polish text typically has 30–50% vowels\n    83→  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYąęóĄĘÓ]/g, \"\").length;\n    84→  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n    85→  if (vowelRatio < 0.15 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n    86→\n    87→  // Single orphaned word ≤3 letters that isn't a common word\n    88→  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n    89→  const COMMON_SHORT = new Set([\n    90→    \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"had\", \"her\",\n    91→    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n    92→    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n    93→    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n    94→  ]);\n    95→  if (words.length === 1 && letters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n    96→    return true;\n    97→  }\n    98→\n    99→  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n   100→  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n   101→    return true;\n   102→  }\n   103→\n   104→  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) — body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n   105→  const trimmed = text.trim();\n   106→  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n   107→    return true;\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n   111→  if (words.length >= 2) {\n   112→    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n   113→      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n   114→      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n   115→      \"w\", \"z\",  // Polish prepositions\n   116→    ]);\n   117→    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n   118→      (w) =>\n   119→        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n   120→        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n   121→        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n   122→    );\n   123→    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n   124→      return true;\n   125→    }\n   126→  }\n   127→\n   128→  return false;\n   129→}\n   130→\n   131→function passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n   132→  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n   133→  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n   134→  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n   135→  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n   136→  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n   137→  // Single-word non-title fragments\n   138→  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n   139→  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;\n   140→  return true;\n   141→}\n   142→\n   143→/**\n   144→ * Detect initial burst of short garbled lines.\n   145→ * Returns the index of the first non-garbled or long line.\n   146→ */\n   147→function findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n   148→  let i = 0;\n   149→  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n   150→    i++;\n   151→  }\n   152→  return i;\n   153→}\n   154→\n   155→function wordCount(text: string): number {\n   156→  return text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0).length;\n   157→}\n   158→\n   159→/**\n   160→ * Build candidate strings from lines: single lines plus multi-line joins (2-3 consecutive).\n   161→ * Skips initial burst of short garbled lines. Scans all remaining lines. Caps at 25.\n   162→ */\n   163→export type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n   164→\n   165→function buildCandidates(\n   166→  lines: Array<string>\n   167→): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n   168→  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   169→\n   170→  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n   171→    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n   172→    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n   173→      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n   174→    }\n   175→  }\n   176→\n   177→  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n   178→  const candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> = [];\n   179→  const seen = new Set<string>();\n   180→\n   181→  for (let i = burstEnd; i < nonEmptyLines.length; i++) {\n   182→    const line = nonEmptyLines[i];\n   183→\n   184→    // Single line\n   185→    if (passesHardFilters(line.text)) {\n   186→      const norm = line.text.toLowerCase();\n   187→      if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   188→        seen.add(norm);\n   189→        candidates.push({ text: line.text, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n   190→      }\n   191→    }\n   192→\n   193→    // 2-line join\n   194→    if (i + 1 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n   195→      const joined2 = `${line.text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text}`;\n   196→      if (passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n   197→        const norm = joined2.toLowerCase();\n   198→        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   199→          seen.add(norm);\n   200→          candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n   201→        }\n   202→      }\n   203→    }\n   204→\n   205→    // 3-line join\n   206→    if (i + 2 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n   207→      const joined3 = `${line.text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 2].text}`;\n   208→      if (passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n   209→        const norm = joined3.toLowerCase();\n   210→        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   211→          seen.add(norm);\n   212→          candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n   213→        }\n   214→      }\n   215→    }\n   216→  }\n   217→\n   218→  // Pre-filter to 25 before embedding calls: prefer ALL_CAPS and short candidates.\n   219→  // Position-based scoring handles final ranking.\n   220→  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n   221→    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n   222→      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n   223→      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n   224→      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n   225→      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n   226→      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n   227→      return aShort - bShort;\n   228→    });\n   229→    return prioritized.slice(0, 25);\n   230→  }\n   231→\n   232→  return candidates;\n   233→}\n   234→\n   235→// Module-level cache for reference embeddings\n   236→let cachedTitleRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   237→let cachedHeaderRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   238→let cachedNoiseRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   239→\n   240→export function _resetEmbeddingCacheForTests(): void {\n   241→  cachedTitleRefEmbedding = null;\n   242→  cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = null;\n   243→  cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = null;\n   244→}\n   245→\n   246→export async function extractTitleWithEmbeddings(\n   247→  text: string,\n   248→  embed: EmbedFn\n   249→): Promise<string | undefined> {\n   250→  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n   251→    return undefined;\n   252→  }\n   253→\n   254→  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\");\n   255→  const candidates = buildCandidates(lines);\n   256→\n   257→  if (candidates.length === 0) {\n   258→    return undefined;\n   259→  }\n   260→\n   261→  // Cache reference embeddings\n   262→  if (!cachedTitleRefEmbedding) {\n   263→    cachedTitleRefEmbedding = await embed(TITLE_REFERENCE);\n   264→  }\n   265→  if (!cachedHeaderRefEmbedding) {\n   266→    cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = await embed(HEADER_REFERENCE);\n   267→  }\n   268→  if (!cachedNoiseRefEmbedding) {\n   269→    cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = await embed(NOISE_REFERENCE);\n   270→  }\n   271→\n   272→  // Find ALL_CAPS candidates with ≥2 words where every significant word has ≥4 alpha letters.\n   273→  // Insignificant tokens (≤1 alpha letter: \"/\", \"&\", \"+\", \":\", \"D)\", etc.) are filtered before\n   274→  // the check so that multi-line joins with continuation punctuation still qualify.\n   275→  const isStructuralHeading = (c: { text: string }): boolean => {\n   276→    if (!isAllCaps(c.text) || wordCount(c.text) < 2) return false;\n   277→    const sigWords = c.text.trim().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length > 1);\n   278→    return sigWords.length >= 2 && sigWords.every((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   279→  };\n   280→\n   281→  // Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates (embedding quality signal)\n   282→  const rawScored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; rawScore: number; embedding: Array<number> }> = [];\n   283→  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n   284→    const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n   285→    const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n   286→    const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n   287→    const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n   288→    const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n   289→    rawScored.push({ text: candidate.text, position: candidate.position, origin: candidate.origin, rawScore, embedding });\n   290→  }\n   291→\n   292→  // Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n   293→  // This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n   294→  const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n   295→\n   296→  // Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n   297→  // if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled.\n   298→  for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n   299→    const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   300→    for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n   301→      if (other === sc) continue;\n   302→      const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   303→      const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n   304→        otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n   305→      );\n   306→      if (hasTruncation) {\n   307→        sc.rawScore -= 0.15;\n   308→        break;\n   309→      }\n   310→    }\n   311→  }\n   312→\n   313→  const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n   314→    ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n   315→    : null;\n   316→  const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n   317→\n   318→  // When the best structural heading has a continuation on the next line introduced by a\n   319→  // punctuation token (/, &, +, :, or parenthesis), prefer the longer 2-line join as the\n   320→  // complete heading. E.g. \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" + \"/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\".\n   321→  // Guard: the remainder after the prefix must start with a continuation character to avoid\n   322→  // merging two separate consecutive recipe titles (FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS stays separate\n   323→  // from FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS because \"FINNISH\" does not start with a continuation token).\n   324→  const firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n   325→    rawScored.find((c) => {\n   326→      if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n   327→      const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   328→      const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n   329→      return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n   330→    }) ?? baseHeading\n   331→  );\n   332→\n   333→  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n   334→  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n   335→    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker — amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n   336→    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n   337→    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n   338→      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n   339→      : 1.0;\n   340→\n   341→    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings\n   342→    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   343→      ? 0.08\n   344→      : 0;\n   345→\n   346→    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n   347→    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n   348→\n   349→    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n   350→    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n   351→    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n   352→    // baseScore excludes position factor — used for diagnostics and ranking\n   353→    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   354→    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   355→    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n   356→  });\n   357→\n   358→  if (scored.length === 0) {\n   359→    return undefined;\n   360→  }\n   361→\n   362→  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n   363→  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n   364→  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n   365→  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n   366→\n   367→  // Filter candidates above threshold\n   368→  let selected = scored.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n   369→\n   370→  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n   371→  // the threshold. Cases:\n   372→  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n   373→  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n   374→  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n   375→  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n   376→  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n   377→  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n   378→    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   379→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   380→      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n   381→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   382→      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n   383→      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n   384→    });\n   385→  }\n   386→\n   387→  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join survived the threshold and its second\n   388→  // part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix so the dedup\n   389→  // \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n   390→  // E.g. \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\" is removed when\n   391→  // \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" also survived (continuation: &).\n   392→  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( — digit continuations\n   393→  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n   394→  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n   395→  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n   396→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   397→      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n   398→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   399→      return !survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n   400→        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n   401→        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n   402→        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n   403→        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n   404→      });\n   405→    });\n   406→  }\n   407→\n   408→  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n   409→  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n   410→  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n   411→  // The pre-filter above handles the conflicting case (structural heading prefix removal) so that\n   412→  // the incomplete prefix line is never present here when the complete join is in selected.\n   413→  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n   414→    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n   415→    return !selected.some(\n   416→      (b) =>\n   417→        b !== a &&\n   418→        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n   419→        b.text.length < a.text.length\n   420→    );\n   421→  });\n   422→\n   423→  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n   424→  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (≥2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n   425→  // A single ALL_CAPS title among mixed-case survivors is a single-recipe page —\n   426→  // collapse to the highest-scoring candidate.\n   427→  // Zero ALL_CAPS survivors → mixed-case multi-title page → keep all.\n   428→  if (selected.length > 1) {\n   429→    const allCapsSelected = selected.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text));\n   430→    if (allCapsSelected.length >= 2) {\n   431→      selected = allCapsSelected;\n   432→    } else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n   433→      selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   434→    }\n   435→  }\n   436→\n   437→  // Cap at 3, sort by document position\n   438→  selected.sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n   439→  selected = selected.slice(0, 3);\n   440→\n   441→  if (selected.length === 0) {\n   442→    return undefined;\n   443→  }\n   444→\n   445→  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n   446→}\n   447→\n   448→/**\n   449→ * Extract potential recipe title from OCR text (sync heuristic fallback)\n   450→ */\n   451→export function extractTitle(text: string): string | undefined {\n   452→  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n   453→    return undefined;\n   454→  }\n   455→\n   456→  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\").map((line) => line.trim());\n   457→\n   458→  for (const line of lines) {\n   459→    if (line.length === 0) continue;\n   460→    if (line.length < 3 || line.length > 50) continue;\n   461→    if (looksLikeIngredient(line)) continue;\n   462→    if (isAllCaps(line)) continue;\n   463→    if (startsWithNumber(line)) continue;\n   464→    return line;\n   465→  }\n   466→\n   467→  return undefined;\n   468→}\n   469→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"220c2158-c29d-4d36-918e-39dcfccb497b","uuid":"2df2b50e-8c17-41c0-94c0-6c358ce78ca9","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts","content":"/**\n * Title Extraction\n * Extracts potential recipe title from OCR text using heuristics or semantic embeddings\n */\n\nimport { cosineSimilarity } from \"./embeddings\";\n\nexport type EmbedFn = (text: string) => Promise<Array<number>>;\n\nconst TITLE_REFERENCE =\n  \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\";\nconst HEADER_REFERENCE =\n  \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\";\nconst NOISE_REFERENCE =\n  \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\";\n\n/**\n * Measurement units commonly found in ingredient lists\n */\nconst MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS = [\n  \"cup\",\n  \"cups\",\n  \"tbsp\",\n  \"tsp\",\n  \"tablespoon\",\n  \"teaspoon\",\n  \"oz\",\n  \"lb\",\n  \"gram\",\n  \"grams\",\n  \"kg\",\n  \"ml\",\n  \"liter\",\n  \"pinch\",\n  \"dash\",\n  \"handful\",\n];\n\n/**\n * Patterns that identify recipe metadata lines (not titles)\n */\nconst METADATA_PATTERNS = [\n  /^(SERVES?|MAKES?|YIELDS?)\\b/i,\n  /^(PREP(ARATION)?|COOK(ING)?|PROOF|RISING|FERMENTATION|REST(ING)?)\\s*(AND\\s*)?(COOK(ING)?)?\\s*TIME/i,\n  /^SAMPLE\\s+SCHEDULE\\b/i,\n  /^BULK\\s+FERMENTATION\\b/i,\n  /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i,\n];\n\n/**\n * Single-word non-title words — standalone OCR fragments unlikely to be recipe titles\n */\nconst NON_TITLE_WORDS = new Set([\n  \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"are\", \"was\",\n  \"has\", \"his\", \"her\", \"its\", \"our\", \"who\", \"how\", \"may\", \"new\", \"now\",\n  \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\", \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n  \"buns\", \"with\",\n]);\n\nfunction looksLikeIngredient(line: string): boolean {\n  const lowerLine = line.toLowerCase();\n  return MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => lowerLine.includes(pattern));\n}\n\nfunction startsWithNumber(line: string): boolean {\n  return /^\\s*\\d/.test(line);\n}\n\nfunction isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n}\n\nfunction looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n}\n\nfunction isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n\n  // Check vowel ratio — English/Polish text typically has 30–50% vowels\n  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYąęóĄĘÓ]/g, \"\").length;\n  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n  if (vowelRatio < 0.15 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n\n  // Single orphaned word ≤3 letters that isn't a common word\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  const COMMON_SHORT = new Set([\n    \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"had\", \"her\",\n    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n  ]);\n  if (words.length === 1 && letters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) — body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n  const trimmed = text.trim();\n  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n  if (words.length >= 2) {\n    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n      \"w\", \"z\",  // Polish prepositions\n    ]);\n    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n      (w) =>\n        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n    );\n    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n      return true;\n    }\n  }\n\n  return false;\n}\n\nfunction passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n  // Single-word non-title fragments\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;\n  return true;\n}\n\n/**\n * Detect initial burst of short garbled lines.\n * Returns the index of the first non-garbled or long line.\n */\nfunction findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n  let i = 0;\n  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n    i++;\n  }\n  return i;\n}\n\nfunction wordCount(text: string): number {\n  return text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0).length;\n}\n\n/**\n * Build candidate strings from lines: single lines plus multi-line joins (2-3 consecutive).\n * Skips initial burst of short garbled lines. Scans all remaining lines. Caps at 25.\n */\nexport type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n\nfunction buildCandidates(\n  lines: Array<string>\n): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n\n  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n  const candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> = [];\n  const seen = new Set<string>();\n\n  for (let i = burstEnd; i < nonEmptyLines.length; i++) {\n    const line = nonEmptyLines[i];\n\n    // Single line\n    if (passesHardFilters(line.text)) {\n      const norm = line.text.toLowerCase();\n      if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n        seen.add(norm);\n        candidates.push({ text: line.text, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 2-line join\n    if (i + 1 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n      const joined2 = `${line.text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text}`;\n      if (passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n        const norm = joined2.toLowerCase();\n        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n          seen.add(norm);\n          candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 3-line join\n    if (i + 2 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n      const joined3 = `${line.text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 2].text}`;\n      if (passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n        const norm = joined3.toLowerCase();\n        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n          seen.add(norm);\n          candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Pre-filter to 25 before embedding calls: prefer ALL_CAPS and short candidates.\n  // Position-based scoring handles final ranking.\n  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      return aShort - bShort;\n    });\n    return prioritized.slice(0, 25);\n  }\n\n  return candidates;\n}\n\n// Module-level cache for reference embeddings\nlet cachedTitleRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\nlet cachedHeaderRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\nlet cachedNoiseRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n\nexport function _resetEmbeddingCacheForTests(): void {\n  cachedTitleRefEmbedding = null;\n  cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = null;\n  cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = null;\n}\n\nexport async function extractTitleWithEmbeddings(\n  text: string,\n  embed: EmbedFn\n): Promise<string | undefined> {\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\");\n  const candidates = buildCandidates(lines);\n\n  if (candidates.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  // Cache reference embeddings\n  if (!cachedTitleRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedTitleRefEmbedding = await embed(TITLE_REFERENCE);\n  }\n  if (!cachedHeaderRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = await embed(HEADER_REFERENCE);\n  }\n  if (!cachedNoiseRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = await embed(NOISE_REFERENCE);\n  }\n\n  // Find ALL_CAPS candidates with ≥2 words where every significant word has ≥4 alpha letters.\n  // Insignificant tokens (≤1 alpha letter: \"/\", \"&\", \"+\", \":\", \"D)\", etc.) are filtered before\n  // the check so that multi-line joins with continuation punctuation still qualify.\n  const isStructuralHeading = (c: { text: string }): boolean => {\n    if (!isAllCaps(c.text) || wordCount(c.text) < 2) return false;\n    const sigWords = c.text.trim().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length > 1);\n    return sigWords.length >= 2 && sigWords.every((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n  };\n\n  // Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates (embedding quality signal)\n  const rawScored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; rawScore: number; embedding: Array<number> }> = [];\n  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n    const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n    const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n    const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n    const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n    const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n    rawScored.push({ text: candidate.text, position: candidate.position, origin: candidate.origin, rawScore, embedding });\n  }\n\n  // Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n  // This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n  const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n\n  // Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n  // if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled.\n  for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n    const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n    for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n      if (other === sc) continue;\n      const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n      const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n        otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n      );\n      if (hasTruncation) {\n        sc.rawScore -= 0.15;\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n    ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n    : null;\n  const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n\n  // When the best structural heading has a continuation on the next line introduced by a\n  // punctuation token (/, &, +, :, or parenthesis), prefer the longer 2-line join as the\n  // complete heading. E.g. \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" + \"/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\".\n  // Guard: the remainder after the prefix must start with a continuation character to avoid\n  // merging two separate consecutive recipe titles (FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS stays separate\n  // from FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS because \"FINNISH\" does not start with a continuation token).\n  const firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n    rawScored.find((c) => {\n      if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n      const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n      const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n      return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n    }) ?? baseHeading\n  );\n\n  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker — amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n      : 1.0;\n\n    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings\n    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n      ? 0.08\n      : 0;\n\n    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n\n    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n    // baseScore excludes position factor — used for diagnostics and ranking\n    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n  });\n\n  if (scored.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n\n  // Filter candidates above threshold\n  let selected = scored.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n\n  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n  // the threshold. Cases:\n  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join survived the threshold and its second\n  // part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix so the dedup\n  // \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n  // E.g. \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\" is removed when\n  // \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" also survived (continuation: &).\n  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( — digit continuations\n  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      return !survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n      });\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n  // The pre-filter above handles the conflicting case (structural heading prefix removal) so that\n  // the incomplete prefix line is never present here when the complete join is in selected.\n  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n    return !selected.some(\n      (b) =>\n        b !== a &&\n        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n        b.text.length < a.text.length\n    );\n  });\n\n  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (≥2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n  // A single ALL_CAPS title among mixed-case survivors is a single-recipe page —\n  // collapse to the highest-scoring candidate.\n  // Zero ALL_CAPS survivors → mixed-case multi-title page → keep all.\n  if (selected.length > 1) {\n    const allCapsSelected = selected.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text));\n    if (allCapsSelected.length >= 2) {\n      selected = allCapsSelected;\n    } else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n      selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Cap at 3, sort by document position\n  selected.sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n  selected = selected.slice(0, 3);\n\n  if (selected.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n}\n\n/**\n * Extract potential recipe title from OCR text (sync heuristic fallback)\n */\nexport function extractTitle(text: string): string | undefined {\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\").map((line) => line.trim());\n\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    if (line.length === 0) continue;\n    if (line.length < 3 || line.length > 50) continue;\n    if (looksLikeIngredient(line)) continue;\n    if (isAllCaps(line)) continue;\n    if (startsWithNumber(line)) continue;\n    return line;\n  }\n\n  return undefined;\n}\n","numLines":469,"startLine":1,"totalLines":469}}}
