{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UbJvz423fkhKZ4hM15cyof","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So iteration 6 improved to 66.7% (4/6 tests passing), but 2 still fail:\n1. `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander` → `(from previous evaluation)` - Hmm, \"(from previous evaluation)\" is interesting. This means the title-loop script is marking these as \"from previous evaluation\". Let me check the title-loop.py script to understand what this means.\n\nActually wait - looking at the results file: `- no` means these still failed. The `(from previous evaluation)` in the \"Got\" field in the task description - that's probably from how the loop script records failures. \n\nI need to look at the actual results.txt file more carefully to see what the model actually produced in iteration 6 for these two failing cases, since the \"(from previous evaluation)\" notation is confusing. Let me trace through the title-loop.py script to understand how it's recording and displaying these outputs.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":314,"cache_read_input_tokens":33083,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":314},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"220c2158-c29d-4d36-918e-39dcfccb497b","uuid":"2927c997-7885-49a4-aa17-b62bfc553850"}
